</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-52_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Agile learning is a mindset and methodology borrowed from the world of software development, where it originated as a response to the limitations of rigid, waterfall-style project management. 
</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-54_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-55_ pf-text-1">According to a report by the Association for Talent Development (ATD), 83% of organisations say that agile approaches are used in some form within their organisation for learning and development.
